unication, teamwork, and supportive management make for a stellar learning environment. As a technical representative, all of the resources I need to carry out any and all job responsibilities are found right at my fingertips. The staff is overwhelmingly helpful to new recruits and everyone wears a warm smile. On the job training, online modules, and courses are fully covered to smooth out the learning process. There's never a shortage of work and those who share the company's work philosophy will be rewarded with a comprehensive bonus plan. The days go by quickly in a highly productive low stress environment. I am positively elated to work with this company. The owner John Gordon and his wife Helen are approachable and easy to talk to, topping off this cake with a sweet finish.ConsYou may be asked to learn up to 2 additional roles, but I see this as less of a burden and more of an opportunity to broaden my skill set.Advice to ManagementKeep up the great work!Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Gordon Document Products Response Mar 15, 2015 – President, CEOThank you for your kind remarks. We are glad you enjoy working at GDP! Gordon Document Products 2015-02-16 06:00 PST Jan 28, 2015 Helpful (1)"New sales management and new sales training makes it an easy pleasurable experience working here."StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Marietta, GACurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Marietta, GARecommendsPositive OutlookI have been working at Gordon Document Products full-time (Less than a year)ProsGood upper managementGreat colleague support systemAssigned territoriesState of the art demonstration showroomGood communication with service and install departmentConsInterview process was long and thorough but well worth itWorking with finance is sometimes difficult but