ies.ConsMr. Gordon is very honest--sometimes to a fault. I personally believe that he may trust people with more credit than they deserve because I have witnessed several other employees who have tried taking advantage of him. I have observed those sample employees not being self-motivated, but instead being extremely lazy and dishonest.Advice to ManagementContinue to hold employees to their job description, and continue to lead by example. Mr. Gordon has the greatest integrity that I have ever had the pleasure of experiencing, and any employee who is willing to work hard & enjoys working for a wonderful employer, then I would recommend anyone work here!Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Gordon Document Products Response Mar 15, 2015 – President, CEOThank you for your reassurances and validation. We continue to work hard to make GDP the best place to work possible. Gordon Document Products 2014-11-23 17:46 PST Nov 12, 2014 Helpful (2)"Work your butt off and get PAID!"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Sales Representative in Marietta, GACurrent Employee - Sales Representative in Marietta, GARecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Gordon Document Products full-time (More than a year)ProsGood oppty to make some good money and help businesses with their current and future needs. Unlike some of the non professionals that just walk in off the street with a proposal in hand for their one size fits all special of the week, GDP enforces a needs analysis policy to show the customer that we customer tailor a system to their needs. GDP hired a new sales MGR who subscribes to this theory and knows how to sell on the up and up.Good spiffs. The Techs are what keep the customers happy. Great techs, great tech service mgr and great tech field mgr. The techs diagnose the problem right the first time, get the parts needed to fix the problem right the first time, and get the job done quickly. The customers appreciate that. And so does the sales force. The owner's wife caters lunch for late morning/early afternoon demonstrations and that is a hit with customers. Personal touch. The woman is pure class, grace and poise.ConsCompany needs a dedicated IT staff that will work their butts off instead of sitting around and complaining. This is a demanding position and is not for every one.Advice to ManagementKeep the spiffs/incentives in place; keep a well balanced inventory/mixture of all lines with different features. Let the sales staff flow and just sit back and watch the magic happen.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Gordon Document Products Response Mar 15, 2015 – President, CEOThank you! We have a great crew today after years of hard work and attracting the right people. We appreciate your contributions and appreciate your comments! Gordon Document Products 2014-11-12 16:49 PST Nov 11, 2014 Helpful (2)"Great Place To Work."StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Marietta, GACurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Marietta, GARecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Gordon Document Products full-time (More than a year)ProsThis is an excellent place to work, with a great deal of opportunity for advancement and earnings. The executive management is fair and easy to work with, always expressing interest in the ideas and feedback of staff members, and they take care of their employees with nice benefits, bonuses & reimbursements. This company is professional in all manners of appearances and behaviors, and I appreciate the quality of character held by Management and staff alike.ConsThere is a lot of unsupervised work, so for people that are not self-disciplined or self-motivated, it is unlikely they will get much done or reach their true potential. This is not a place of employment for those that need to be micro managed.Advice to ManagementPost and advise staff of possible advancements and provide incentives for staff to aim higher.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (2) Gordon Document Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Gordon Document Products 2014-11-11 14:28 PST Aug 20, 2014 Helpful (3)"Great Place To Work"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Atlanta, GACurrent Employee - Sales Executive in Atlanta, GARecommendsPositive OutlookApproves of CEOI have been working at Gordon Document Products full-time (More than 3 years)ProsAs an employee of Gordon Document Products going on 4 years my experience here has been a positive one. It is a great place if you're self motivated, a hard worker and don't require a lot of supervision. The culture here is up beat and the management team will supply you with all the tools you need to be successful. The owner will personally go on sales calls with you to help close deals. The company has sent me to all the manufacturer's training programs to enhance my sales skills. The commission pay is very fast compared to most sales jobs I've had in the past.ConsIt can seems like your being micro managed if you're not meeting the minimum company expectations.Advice to ManagementI would like to see a more lucrative plan for tenured sales reps.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (3) Gordon Document Products Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Gordon Document Products 2014-08-20 16:51 PDT Showing 17 of 24 reviewsReset FiltersPrevious12NextRevie